KADUNA â€“ PDP Presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar and Labour Party candidate Peter Obi came first and second respectively in one of the polling units inside the Kaduna State Government House in the presidential election held on Saturday (today). Bola Tinubu of the ruling All Progressives Congress came third in the Government House polling unit that has Nasir el-Rufai of APC as governor. The booth, Unit 013 is one of the polling units inside the Kaduna State Government House. The result from the booth, Unit 013 signed by the presiding officer, Kalu kelechi Micheal, showed that the APC scored 40, Labour party scored 48, PDP 69, while NNPP had 11. Governor Nasir el-Rufai of Kaduna is one of the lead campaigners of Tinubu.